==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Thole
<hw>Thole</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>thowel</asp>, and <asp>thowl</asp>.]</altsp> <ety>[OE.
<ets>thol</ets>, AS. <ets>⟦thorn⟧ol</ets>; akin to D. <ets>dol</ets>,
Icel. <ets>⟦thorn⟧ollr</ets> a fir tree, a young fir, a tree, a
thole.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A wooden or metal pin, set in the gunwale
of a boat, to serve as a fulcrum for the oar in rowing.</def>
<rj><au>Longfellow.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The pin, or handle, of a scythe snath.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Thole pin</b></col>. <cd>Same as
<er>Thole</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thole</ent>⟦br⟧

